The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Monday, January 13, 2003  Inside Story works well 
 BY OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT				 	 Bold Chieftan				 										Calcutta: Inside Story, Affined, River Melody and Bold Chieftan were impressive from among the following horses seen exercising on Saturday morning:				 										Outer sand track				 										1,600m: Inside Story (C. Alford) and Affined (Shanker) in 2-3s; (1,000m) 1-14s; (400m) 31s. Former was a length better. Both moved well.				 										1,400m: Sea Royale (C. Alford) in 1-48s; (1,000m) 1-16s; (400m) 32s. Eased up in last part..				 										1,200m: Acklins (Rb) in 1-30s; (800m) 1-1s; (400m) 32s. Easy. Spanish Drums (Salam) in 1-31s; (800m) 59s; (400m) 28s. Moved well. Admirer (Domingo) in 1-35s; (400m) 33s. Very easy. Buffalo Park (Saran) and Comedy of Errors (Rutherford) 1-35s; (400m) 32s. They were easy as they levelled. Alexine (C. Alford) and Idolize (Shanker) in 1-30s; (800m) 1-0s; (400m) 31s. They moved well as they levelled. 				 										1,000m: Adams Dream (Kujur) and Secret Desire (A. P. Singh) in 1-15s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 29s. They were handy as they levelled. 				 										800m: Streak (Rb) and Akebono (Maseyk) in 59s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 29s. They were easy as they levelled. River Melody (Merchant) in 58s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 27s. Good. Asprey (Jaiswal) in 59s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 28s. Was urged. King Nicholas (Merchant) and Gallant Romeo (Upadhya) in 57s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 29s. They were level and they moved well. Timbavati (Kujur) in 57s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 29s. Fit. Revolution (Kujur) in 1-1s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 30s. 				 										600m: Imperial Pearl (Upadhya) and Great Ambition (Merchant) in 43s; (400m) 29s They were level. Rhythm Divine (Engineer) in 43s; (400m) 29s. Magical Strike (R. Ahmed) and Direct Access (Upadhya) im 44s; (400m) 30s. Tghey moved well as they levelled. Beneficent (Merchant) and Autumn Fantasy (Amil) in 46s; (400m) 29s. They were level.				 										Sand track				 										1,400m: Abandoned (Brij S.) in 1-35s; (1,000m) 1-11s; (400m) 30s. Eased up in last part.				 										800m: Bold Chieftan (Merchant) in 52s; (600m) 37s; (400m) 24s. Was handy. Royal Satin (Saran) in 52s; (600m) 38s; (400m) 25s. A three-year-old by Gold Discovery/Spiritual Vibration (Kumar) in 37s; (400m) 23s. Good. Grecian (Rb) in 55s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 26s. 				 										600m: Sariano (Saran) and Sweet Revenge (Tamang) in 41s; (400m) 27s. They were level.
